## 🚫 Common Mistakes

❌ Storing tokens in localStorage (XSS risk)  
❌ Handling passwords in React  
❌ No route protection  
❌ API calls without auth headers

***

## ✅ Interview‑Ready Answer (Perfect)

> **Authentication in React is implemented by delegating credential validation to the backend, storing the authenticated user or token securely (usually via context or cookies), protecting routes using conditional rendering or guards, and attaching tokens to API requests to authorize access.**

***

## ✅ Real‑World Best Practice Summary

✅ Backend handles security  
✅ React manages auth state  
✅ Context for global access  
✅ Protected routes  
✅ Cookies over localStorage  
✅ SSR validation when possible

